d%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20statement%20added%20that%20the%20departure%20of%20Afghan%20diplomats%20%E2%80%9Ccoincides%20with%20numerous%20diplomats%20coincides%20with%20an%20increasingly%20untenable%20situation%20in%20India%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIt%20went%20on%20to%20say%20that%20threats%20to%20families%20back%20in%20Afghanistan%20from%20the%20Taliban%2C%20as%20well%20as%2C%20a%20lack%20of%20support%20from%20the%20Indian%20government%20led%20to%20this%20decision.%20%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20regrettable%20that%20India%20is%20not%20extending%20rightful%20visa%20renewals%20for%20Afghan%20diplomats%2C%20let%20alone%20considering%20their%20continued%20presence.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20statement%20also%20said%20that%20conditions%20faced%20by%20Afghan%20refugees%20in%20India%20highlight%20the%20%E2%80%9Cconcerning%20aspect%E2%80%9D%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20non-membership%20in%20the%20Geneva%20Convention%20and%20its%20stance%20on%20asylum%20for%20Afghan%20citizens%20is%20a%20concerning%20aspect.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Afghan%20ambassador%E2%80%99s%20statement%20seems%20to%20be%20in%20response%20to%20remarks%20by%20Indian%20official%20sources%2C%20who%20had%20pointed%20out%20that%20the%20current%20letter%20seems%20to%20be%20%E2%80%9Cin%20context%20of%20the%20Ambassador%20being%20out%20of%20India%20for%20past%20many%20months%2C%20steady%20departure%20of%20diplomats%20to%20third%20countries%20reportedly%20after%20receiving%20asylum%20as%20well%20as%20reports%20of%20infighting%20amongst%20Embassy%20personnel%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20Taliban%20took%20over%20in%20August%202021%2C%20India%20had%20evacuated%20its%20embassy%20in%20Kabul.%20However%2C%20India%20was%20back%20in%20Kabul%20in%20June%202022%20with%20a%20%E2%80%98technical%20team%E2%80%99%20made%20up%20of%20diplomats%20and%20security%20personnel.%20It%20had%20to%20work%20as%20a%20%E2%80%98de-facto%E2%80%99%20embassy%20as%20India%2C%20just%20like%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20international%20community%2C%20does%20not%20recognise%20the%20Taliban%20regime.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Afghan%20embassy%20in%20New%20Delhi%20continued%20to%20operate%20after%20the%20fall%20of%20the%20Islamic%20Republic%2C%20but%20did%20not%20recognise%20the%20Taliban%20regime.%20In%20May%20this%20year%2C%20the%20Taliban%20regime%20finally%20sent%20a%20directive%20that%20Farid%20Mamundzay%2C%20appointed%20by%20the%20previous%20Islamic%20Republic%2C%20should%20be%20removed%20and%20replaced%20with%20another%20diplomat%20as%C2%A0%3Cem%3ECharge%20D%E2%80%99affaires%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20Taliban-appointed%20diplomat%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fafghan-embassy-taliban-farid-mamundzay-mohammad-qadir-shah%5C%22%3Enot%20allowed%20to%20take%20charge%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20his%20other%20colleagues%20when%20Mamundzay%20had%20been%20out%20of%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20embassy%20in%20New%20Delhi%20received%20cold%20treatment%20from%20the%20Indian%20government%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.facebook.com%2FAfghanistanINHyderabad%2Fposts%2Fpfbid02NWjYn37LEdsiNePt4iemiFUz8ayNfAbKMPA6faHRTbxJniMMMiiGNBBEcdp5dQP1l%5C%22%3Ethe%20consul%20generals%3C%2Fa%3E%20met%20with%20a%20senior%20official%20in%20the%20Ministry%20of%20External%20Affairs%20to%20discuss%20issues%20related%20to%20Afghan%20nationals%20in%20India%20earlier%20this%20month.%20The%20two%20consulates%20in%20Mumbai%20and%20Hyderabad%20had%20also%20taken%20part%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2FHafizZiaAhmad1%2Fstatus%2F1676168696195153920%3Fs%3D20%5C%22%3Emeetings%20chaired%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20the%20Taliban%20foreign%20minister%2C%20Amir%20Khan%20Muttaqi%2C%20unlike%20their%20colleagues%20in%20New%20Delhi%20who%20ignored%20any%20instructions%20from%20Kabul.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOn%20Friday%2C%20the%20two%20consulates%20issued%20a%20joint%20notice%20on%20their%20Facebook%20page%20on%20Friday%20rejecting%20%E2%80%9Crumours%E2%80%9D%20th