t%20make%20and%20sell%20their%20own%20bread.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20unclear%20how%20restaurant%20chains%20like%20Panera%20Bread%20came%20to%20be%20exempt%20from%20the%20fast-food%20law.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat's%20part%20of%20the%20sausage-making%2C%26quot%3B%20Newsom%20said%20when%20asked%20about%20the%20quirky%20exemption%20during%20a%20press%20conference.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20establishment%20that%20bakes%20bread%20for%20sale%20on%20its%20premises%20is%20not%20considered%20a%20fast-food%20restaurant%2C%20the%20new%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fleginfo.legislature.ca.gov%2Ffaces%2FbillTextClient.xhtml%3Fbill_id%3D202320240AB1228%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elaw%3C%2Fa%3E%20states.%20%26quot%3BThis%20exemption%20applies%20only%20where%20the%20establishment%20produces%20for%20sale%20bread%20as%20a%20stand-alone%20menu%20item%2C%20and%20does%20not%20apply%20if%20the%20bread%20is%20available%20for%20sale%20solely%20as%20part%20of%20another%20menu%20item.%26quot%3B%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECalifornia's%20current%20minimum%20wage%20is%20%2415.50.%20It%20goes%20up%20to%20%2416%20an%20hour%20in%20January.%20Under%20the%20new%20law%20signed%20by%20Newsom%2C%20thousands%20of%20fast-food%20workers%20making%20minimum%20wage%20in%20the%20state%20will%20get%20another%20increase%20to%20%2420%20an%20hour%20in%20April.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20new%20law%20replaces%20the%20controversial%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgavin-newsom-fast-food-bill-raise-minimum-wage-workers-2022-9%3Fr%3DUS%26IR%3DT%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFAST%20Recovery%20Act%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20called%20for%20the%20minimum%20wage%20for%20fast%20food%20workers%20to%20increase%20to%20%2422%20an%20hour%20in%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENewsom%20signed%20the%20FAST%20Act%20into%20law%20last%20year.%20But%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmcdonalds-exec-slams-california-lawmakers-for-passing-fast-food-law-2023-1%23%3A~%3Atext%3DAccording%2520to%2520financial%2520disclosures%252C%2520Erlinger%2Ccomplete%2520compensation%2520history%2520is%2520available.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecorporate%20chains%20such%20as%20McDonald's%2C%20Chipotle%2C%20and%20Chick-fil-A%2C%20and%20franchise%20advocacy%20groups%20fought%20the%20law%3C%2Fa%3E.%20A%20coalition%20of%20restaurant%20industry%20organizations%2C%20who%20said%20the%20law%20could%20raise%20costs%20for%20fast-food%20restaurants%20by%20%243%20billion%2C%20rallied%20to%20get%20a%20referendum%20on%20the%20ballot.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20new%20law%2C%20AB%201228%2C%20represents%20a%20compromise%20between%20labor%20unions%20representing%20fast%20food%20workers%20and%20the%20restaurant%20industry.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBesides%20dropping%20the%20minimum%20wage%20boost%20to%20%2420%20an%20hour%2C%20the%20new%20law%20allows%20a%20fast-food%20council%20to%20adjust%20only%20wages.%20In%20the%20previous%20legislation%2C%20the%20panel%20had%20more%20powers%20over%20workplace%20conditions%2C%20training%2C%20and%20working%20conditions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20council%20can%20increase%20the%20minimum%20wage%20yearly%20by%20up%20to%203.5%25%20or%20the%20change%20in%20the%20US%20consumer%20price%20index%2C%20whichever%20is%20less.%20The%20FAST%20Act%20exempted%20bakeries%20that%20make%20and%20sell%20bread%2C%20and%20that%20provision%20remained%20in%20the%20new%20bill.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENewsom%20said%20the%20Panera%20and%20Boudin%20exemption%20was%20part%20of%20the%20%26quot%3Boriginal%20bill%2C%20and%20we%20went%20back%20and%20forth%2C%20and%20that%20was%20part%20of%20the%20negotiation.%20It's%20the%20nature%20of%20negotiation%20trying%20to%20get%20a%20referendum%20off%20the%20ballot.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpanera-bread-workers-exempt-from-california-fast-food-pay-increase-2023-9%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696006390000%2C%22vi