%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20Thursday%20note%2C%20strategists%20led%20by%20Jan%20Hatzius%20pointed%20to%20concerns%20around%20recent%20pay%20increases%20that%20unions%20like%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2Fwarner-bros-paramount-stock-hollywood-writers-deal-disney-amc-streaming-2023-9%5C%22%3EWriters%20Guild%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20secured%2C%20and%20whether%20they%20could%20potentially%20spark%20a%20rebound%20in%20inflation.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20instead%20see%20the%20recent%20wage%20gains%20for%20union%20workers%20as%20a%20lagging%20indicator%20%E2%80%94%20the%20final%20echo%20of%20last%20year's%20inflation%20surge%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20strategists%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnions%20have%20bargaining%20power%20in%20withholding%20labor%2C%20which%20can%20make%20it%20seem%20like%20union%20employees%20hold%20significant%20sway%20in%20the%20wage-price%20feedback%20loop.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20hasn't%20proven%20to%20be%20true%20in%20the%201960s%20and%201970s%2C%20the%20bank%20said%2C%20when%20high%20inflation%20and%20a%20tight%20labor%20market%20boosted%20wage%20growth%20about%20the%20same%20amount%20for%20union%20and%20non-union%20workers.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221585%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Goldman%20Sachs%20union%20workers%20pay%20wage%20gains%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6516e9e4f5d0bb0019e5b1ca%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22955%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EUnions%20have%20recently%20won%20their%20largest%20wage%20increases%20in%20decades.%3Cp%3EGoldman%20Sachs%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20possible%20that%20recent%20wage%20gains%20could%20push%20overall%20wage%20growth%20slightly%20higher%2C%20but%20the%20ultimate%20impact%20will%20remain%20small%2C%20in%20Goldman's%20view.%20The%20share%20of%20unionized%20employees%20in%20the%20workforce%20is%20modest%2C%20the%20firm%20said%2C%20at%20about%2010%25%2C%20and%20th