0up%20when%20food%20is%20taken%20outdoors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKeeping%20your%20hands%20clean%20when%20handling%20food%20is%20key%20to%20not%20getting%20sick%2C%20but%20how%20often%20do%20you%20find%20hot%20running%20water%20and%20soap%20in%20a%20park%20or%20on%20a%20beach%3F%20You%20can%20use%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Fbest-hand-sanitizers%5C%22%3Ealcohol%20hand%20gels%3C%2Fa%3E%20(they're%20better%20than%20nothing)%2C%20but%20they%20don't%20kill%20all%20germs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlso%2C%20food%20tends%20to%20attract%20an%20array%20of%20flying%20and%20crawling%20critters%2C%20such%20as%20flies%2C%20wasps%20and%20ants%2C%20all%20of%20which%20can%20transfer%20germs%2C%20including%C2%A0%3Cem%3EE%20coli%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcdc-onions-salmonella-mexico-652-people-sick-throw-away-2021-10%5C%22%3ESalmonella%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0and%C2%A0%3Cem%3EListeria%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20to%20your%20food.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKeeping%20perishable%20food%20cold%20and%20covered%20is%20essential%20as%20germs%20can%20double%20in%20numbers%20if%20food%20is%20allowed%20to%20warm%20up%20to%2030%E2%84%83%20for%20more%20than%20a%20few%20hours.%20For%20barbecues%2C%20meat%20needs%20to%20be%20thoroughly%20cooked%2C%20and%20a%20meat%20thermometer%20is%20a%20good%20investment%20to%20avoid%20food%20poisoning.%20Do%20not%20eat%20meat%20if%20its%20internal%20temperature%20is%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.betterhealth.vic.gov.au%2Fhealth%2Fhealthyliving%2Ffood-safety-outdoors%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eless%20than%2070%E2%84%83%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225473%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Various%20salads%20are%20served%20at%20a%20buffet%20during%20a%20corporate%20event.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6516eec7b4518a00191e6f5d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222736%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EVarious%20salads%20are%20served%20at%20a%20buffet%20during%20a%20corporate%20event.%3Cp%3ESilas%20Stein%2Fpicture%20alliance%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3EBuffets%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EKnowing%20what%20food-related%20conditions%20bacteria%20prefer%20to%20grow%20in%2C%20I%20am%20very%20mindful%20of%20the%20microbiological%20safety%20of%20hot%20and%20cold%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fworst-foods-to-eat-at-buffets-food-safety-experts-2019-7%5C%22%3Ebuffet%20displays%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIndoors%2C%20food%20can%20be%20exposed%20to%20contamination%20from%20insects%2C%20dust%20and%20above%20all%2C%20people.%20Food%20poisoning%20is%2C%20therefore%2C%20an%20inevitable%20risk%20when%20dining%20at%20a%C2%A0buffet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EContamination%20comes%20from%20buffet%20visitors%20touching%20food%2C%20and%20germs%20can%20be%20sprayed%20on%20to%20buffets%20from%20people%20sneezing%20or%20coughing%20close%20to%20the%20food.%20Even%20indoors%2C%20one%20must%20consider%20contamination%20by%20insects%2C%20such%20as%20flies%20or%20wasps%2C%20settling%20on%20the%20uncovered%20food.%20Also%2C%20germs%20may%20be%20deposited%20from%20the%20air%2C%20which%20is%20rich%20in%20bacteria%2C%20fungi%20and%20viruses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20always%20look%20at%20the%20clock%20when%20I'm%20at%20a%20buffet%20as%20there%20is%20a%C2%A0two-hour%20catering%20rule%3A%20perishable%20food%20will%20become%20unsafe%20to%20eat%20within%20two%20hours%20if%20not%20kept%20covered%20and%20refrigerated.%20The%20problem%20is%20buffets%20tend%20to%20be%20laid%20out%20before%20you%20arrive%2C%20so%20it%20is%20difficult%20to%20tell%20if%20the%20platters%20of%20cooked%20meat%2C%20seafood%2C%20salads%2C%20desserts%20and%20appetisingly%20arranged%20fruit%20and%20vegetables%20will%20have%20been%20sitting%20for%20more%20than%20two%20hours%20when%20you%20come%20to%20eat%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20hot%20buffets%2C%20such%20as%20those%20served%20at%20breakfast%20in%20hotels%2C%20I%20always%20avoid%20lukewarm%20food%2C%20as%20bacteria%20that%20cause%20food%20poisoning%20can%20grow%20quickly%20when%20food%20is%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.fda.gov%2Ffood%2Fbuy-store-serve-safe-food%2Fserving-safe-buffets%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ekept%20at%20less%20than%2060%E2%84%83%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Hot%20food%20should%20be%20served%20hot%2C%20that%20is%20at%20a%20temperature%20of%20at%20least%2060%E2%84%83.%20If%20there%20is%20any%20uncertainty%20about%20the%20safety%20of%20the%20food%20on%20offer%2C%20I%20reluctantly%20breakfast%20on%20freshly%20toasted%20bread%20and%20individually%20packaged%20marmalade.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221983%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22oysters%20beach%20san%20pancho%20mexico%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F63cafd744b86730019cc123f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221487%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EFresh%20local%20oysters%20purchased%20on%20the%20beach%20in%20San%20Pancho.%3Cp%3ELisa%20Marion%20Smith%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3EOysters%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20some%20foods%20I%20never%20eat%2C%20and%20raw%20shellfish%2C%20such%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fwhy-you-should-avoid-raw-oysters-food-safety-expert-2022-7%5C%22%3Eoysters%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20is%20one%20of%20them.%20This%20is%20because%20oysters%20are%20filter%20feeders%20and%20can%20concentrate%20germs%2C%20such%20as%20%3Cem%3EVibrio%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0and%20norovirus%2C%20in%20their%20tissue.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%C2%A0%3Cem%3EVibrio%3C%2Fem%3E-contaminated%20oyster%20does%20not%20look%2C%20smell%2C%20or%20taste%20different%2C%20but%20can%20still%20make%20you%20very%20ill.%20The%20US%20Centers%20for%20Disease%20Control%20and%20Prevention%20estimates%20that%20about%2080%2C000%20people%20get%C2%A0%3Cem%3EVibrio%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0infections%20from%20raw%20oysters%2C%20and%20in%20the%20US%20alone%20100%20people%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cdc.gov%2Ffoodsafety%2Fcommunication%2Foysters-and-vibriosis.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edie%20from%20vibriosis%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0each%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20also%20possible%20to%20pick%20up%20food%20poisoning%20from%20eating%20any%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fseafood-cooking-tips-mistake-from-michelin-starred-chef-2023-8%5C%22%3Eraw%20shellfish%3C%2Fa%3E%20(clams%2C%20mussels%2C%20whelks%2C%20cockles).%20I%20only%20eat%20shellfish%20that%20are%20well-cooked%20because%20heat%20effectively%20kills%20harmful%20germs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221953%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22romaine%20e%20coli%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6516ee3ff5d0bb0019e5b365%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221465%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ELarge%20scale%20E.%20coli%20outbreaks%20have%20been%20traced%20back%20to%20lettuce.%3Cp%3EGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3EBagged%20salads%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20never%20eat%20bagged%20salads%2C%20largely%20because%20one%20of%20my%20research%20areas%20is%20fresh%20salad%20safety.%20It%20has%20been%20found%20that%20bagged%20lettuce%20can%20contain%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fecoli-romaine-lettuce-outbreak-from-salinas-what-is-ecoli-2019-11%5C%22%3Efood%20poisoning%20germs%3C%2Fa%3E%20such%20as%20%3Cem%3EE%20coli%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%C2%A0%3Cem%3ESalmonella%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0and%C2%A0%3Cem%3EListeria%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20research%20group%C2%A0has%20found%C2%A0that%20these%20pathogens%20grow%20more%20than%20a%20thousand%20times%20better%20when%20given%20juices%20from%20salad%20leaves%2C%20even%20if%20the%20salad%20bag%20is%20refrigerated.%20Worryingly%2C%20the%20same%20germs%20use%20the%20salad%20juices%20to%20become%20more%20virulent%2C%20and%20so%20better%20at%20causing%20an%20infection.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20those%20salad%20lovers%20alarmed%20by%20this%20information%2C%20most%20bagged%20salads%20are%20safe%20if%20stored%20refrigerated%2C%20washed%20well%20before%20use%20(even%20ready-to-eat%20salad%20should%20be%20washed)%20and%20eaten%20as%20soon%20as%20possible%20after%20buying%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222286%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22E.%20coli%20bacteria%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F62fd4727ec781d0018688506%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221715%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20laboratory%20worker%20looks%20for%20strains%20of%20E.coli%20bacteria%20in%20vegetable%20cells%20placed%20in%20a%20petri%20dish.%3Cp%3EFrancisco%20Bonilla%2FReuters%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3ECooking%20practices%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20terms%20of%20cooking%20practices%2C%20I%20have%20a%20list%20of%20dos%20and%20don'ts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20perishable%20foods%2C%20I%20regularly%20check%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Ffoods-you-can-ignore-expiration-dates-2018-11%5C%22%3Euse-by%20dates%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20if%20it%20is%20before%20the%20expiry%20date%20and%20the%20food%20package%20looks%20swollen%2C%20or%20when%20opened%20the%20food%20looks%20or%20smells%20different%20than%20expected%2C%20I%20throw%20it%20in%20the%20bin%20as%20it%20could%20be%20contaminated.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20never%20use%20the%20same%20chopping%20boards%20for%20raw%20and%20cooked%20foods%2C%20and%20washing%20my%20hands%20before%20and%20after%20handling%20food%20is%20instinctual.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20my%20%26quot%3Bnever%20do%26quot%3B%20practices%20is%20reheating%20cooked%20rice.%20This%20is%20because%20uncooked%20rice%20can%20contain%20spores%20of%C2%A0%3Cem%3EBacillus%20cereus%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20a%20food-poisoning%20germ.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlthough%20the%C2%A0%3Cem%3EBacillus%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0cells%20are%20killed%20by%20cooking%2C%20the%20spores%20survive.%20If%20the%20rice%20is%20left%20to%20cool%20and%20sit%20at%20room%20temperature%2C%C2%A0the%20spores%20grow%20into%20bacteria%2C%20which%20will%20increase%20in%20numbers%20quickly%20as%20rice%20is%20a%20good%C2%A0%3Cem%3EBacillus%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0culture%20medium%20when%20at%20room%20temperature.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20rice-cultured%C2%A0%3Cem%3EBacillus%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0can%20produce%20toxins%20that%2C%20within%20a%20few%20hours%20of%20ingestion%2C%20can%20cause%20vomiting%20and%20diarrhoea%20lasting%20up%20to%2024%20hours.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EDining%20out%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20find%20that%20having%20a%20high%20level%20of%20food%20safety%20awareness%20causes%20me%20to%20be%20first%20in%20line%20for%20buffets%2C%20to%20be%20cautious%20about%20eating%20from%20breakfast%20bars%2C%20and%20to%20watch%20the%20clock%20for%20how%20often%20perishable%20food%20is%20replaced.%20I%20never%20collect%20%26quot%3Bdoggy%20bags%26quot%3B%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fhow-to-know-if-leftovers-are-bad-2019-1%5C%22%3Efood%20leftovers%3C%2Fa%3E%20(they%20have%20usually%20exceeded%20the%20two-hour%20time%20limit)%2C%20even%20if%20they%20really%20are%20intended%20for%20a%20pet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20benefits%20of%20being%20a%20microbiologist%20are%20that%20we%20know%20how%20to%20avoid%20food%20poisoning%20and%2C%20in%20return%2C%20people%20have%20confidence%20our%20cooking%20is%20very%20safe%20to%20eat.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EDisclosure%3A%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3EPrimrose%20Freestone%20has%20previously%20received%20funding%20from%20the%20BBSRC%20for%20her%20salad%20research%20work.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EPrimrose%20Freestone%20is%20a%20Senior%20Lecturer%20in%20Clinical%20Microbiology%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Leicester.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicrobiologist-how-to-avoid-food-poisoning-2023-9%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696005506000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6516edd2b4518a00191e6ee