d%20the%20kind%20of%20people%20employed%20by%20them.%20It%20still%20highlights%20the%20continued%20stronghold%20of%20elite%20groups%20in%20the%20entrepreneurial%20sector.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20summation%2C%20the%20report%20brings%20to%20light%20the%20stark%20disparities%20between%20the%20privileged%20and%20underprivileged%20classes%2C%20on%20the%20lines%20of%20caste%2C%20gender%2C%20and%20religion.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWage%20gaps%20have%20a%20significant%20impact%20on%20people%E2%80%99s%20lives%2C%20leading%20to%20poverty%2C%20inequality%2C%20and%20social%20exclusion%2C%20and%20closing%20this%20gap%20requires%20comprehensive%20policy-based%20interventions.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EAmisha%20Singh%20and%20Aditi%20Desai%20are%20research%20analysts%20with%20CNES%20and%20team%20leads%20for%20its%20InfoSphere%20initiative.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EDeepanshu%20Mohan%20is%20professor%20of%20Economics%20and%20director%20at%20the%20Centre%20for%20New%20Economics%20Studies%2C%20O.P.%20Jindal%20Global%20University.%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cem%3EHe%20is%20an%20Honorary%20Research%20Fellow%20with%20Birkbeck%2C%20University%20of%20London%20(2023)%20and%20a%20Visiting%20Professor%20at%20the%20School%20of%20International%20Development%20and%20Global%20Studies%2C%20University%20of%20Ottawa.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1695999611000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F27133636%2F6283735999_47c3124b38_c.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flabour%2Fnew-report-reveals-stark-disparities-in-indias-labour-market-based-on-caste-gender-and-religion%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20largest%20earnings%20gap%20is%20based%20on%20gender%2C%20with%20women%20reporting%20earnings%20at%20only%2040%25%20of%20those%20of%20men%20in%20self-employment%2C%20followed%20by%2064%25%20of%20men%20in%20casual%20wage%20jobs%2C%20and%2076%25%20of%20men%20in%20regular%20wage%20jobs.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22