5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22504%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1695992443000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F29181817%2Fmaxresdefault.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fvideo%2Fwatch-does-india-have-a-colonial-consitituion-or-is-that-a-mistaken-view%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Arghya%20Sengupta%20explains%20why%20he%20believes%20India%E2%80%99s%20constitution%20is%20colonial%20and%20responds%20to%20a%20series%20of%20questions%20challenging%20his%20view%20and%20also%20the%20arguments%20upon%20which%20it%20is%20based.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fvideo%2Fwatch-does-india-have-a-colonial-consitituion-or-is-that-a-mistaken-view%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22The%20Women%20of%20the%20Women%E2%80%99s%20Reservation%20Bill%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F30153449%2FACF098D3-6123-4B67-A2E4-DCA712B4.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20is%20the%20second%20in%20a%20two-part%20series%20by%20the%20author%20on%20the%20women%E2%80%99s%20reservation%20Bill.%20Read%20the%20first%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwomen%2Fbetween-history-and-histrionics%5C%22%3Ehere%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Modi-led%20government%20may%20have%20been%20under%20its%20own%20compulsions%20to%20adopt%20the%20women%E2%80%99s%20reservation%20Bill%20with%20an%20eye%20on%20the%20next%20elections%20but%20the%20discussion%20on%20the%20need%20for%20reservations%20for%20women%20has%20a%20long%20history.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20is%20well-known%2C%20during%20the%20freedom%20struggle%20and%20in%20the%20Constituent%20Assembly%2C%20women%20members%20vociferously%20argued%20against%20reservation%20with%20former%20Lok%20Sabha%20member%20Renuka%20Ray%20decisively%20stating%20that%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9Cwhen%20there%20is%20reservation%20of%20seats%20for%20women%2C%20the%20question%20of%20their%20consideration%20for%20general%20seats%2C%20however%20competent%20they%20may%20be%2C%20does%20not%20usually%20arise.%20We%20feel%20that%20women%20will%20get%20more%20chances%20if%20the%20consideration%20is%20of%20ability%20alone.%E2%80%9D%20Reservation%2C%20she%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Floksabha.nic.in%2Fwritereaddata%2Fcadebatefiles%2FC18071947.html%2520accessed%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eargued%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20would%20be%20%E2%80%98an%20impediment%20to%20our%20growth%20and%20an%20insult%20to%20our%20very%20intelligence%20and%20capacity.%E2%80%99%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20the%20context%20of%20the%20passage%20of%20the%20128%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eth%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20Amendment%2C%20it%20is%20important%20to%20contextualise%20the%20shift%20in%20the%20debate%20in%20women%E2%80%99s%20movement%20in%20the%20post-independence%20period.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20was%20in%201974%20that%20the%20Committee%20on%20the%20Status%20of%20Women%20in%20India%20undertook%20the%20most%20comprehensive%20review%20of%20women%E2%80%99s%20status%20since%20independence.%20The%20report%20made%20a%20specific%20note%20of%20the%20%E2%80%9Cdifficulties%20being%20experienced%20by%20women%20in%20obtaining%20adequate%20representation%E2%80%9D%20and%20the%20%E2%80%9Cdeclining%20trend%20in%20the%20number%20of%20women%20legislators%E2%80%9D%20which%20may%20result%20in%20women%20%E2%80%9Closing%20faith%20in%20the%20political%20process%20to%20change%20their%20conditions%20in%20life%2C%20%5Band%5D%20may%20opt%20out%20of%20the%20political%20system%20and%20become%20either%20passive%20partners%20or%20rebels.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22auto%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EHowever%20the%20members%20of%20the%20committee%20chose%20not%20to%20recommend%20reservations%2C%20prompting%20two%20of%20its%20members%20to%20submit%20a%20dissent%20note.%20%3Cspan%3EIn%20the%20note%2C%20professors%20Lotika%20Sarkar%20and%20Vina%20Mazumdar%20(the%20latter%20was%20also%20the%20member%20secretary%20of%20the%20committee)%20pointed%20out%20that%20despite%20never%20having%20been%20supporters%20of%20special%20representation%20or%20class%20representation%20in%20any%20form%2C%20they%20were%20compelled%20to%20confront%20the%20question%20and%20disagree%20with%20the%20majority%20view%20in%20the%20committee%20because%20%E2%80%9Ca%20political%20system%20cannot%20be%20based%20on%20ideology%20alone%20but%20must%20keep%20in%20touch%20with%20the%20actualities%20of%20the%20social%20situation%20and%20so%20adjust%20its%20operation%20as%20to%20achieve%20the%20desired%20goals%20of%20the%20society.%20The%20mechanics%20of%20the%20system%2C%20if%20they%20do%20not%20grapple%20with%20the%20needs%20of%20a%20society%2C%20can%20defeat%20the%20ultimate%20objective%20in%20the%20long%20run.%20It%20is%20for%20this%20reason%20that%20we%20are%20compelled%20to%20dissent%20from%20the%20Committee%E2%80%99s%20decision%20on%20this%20point.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThese%20observations%20facilitated%20a%20long%20term%20discussion%20on%20women%E2%80%99s%20participation%20in%20political%20bodies%20with%20special%20focus%20on%20local%20bodies.%20They%20drew%20on%20discussions%20with%20regard%20to%20the%20Panchayati%20Raj%20system%2C%20the%20principle%20of%20financial%20devolution%20as%20part%20of%20the%20governance%20to%20advance%20the%20principles%20of%20federalism%20and%2C%20starting%20with%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EAshok%20Mehta%20Committee%20in%201977%2C%20these%20aspects%20were%20the%20subject%20of%20debate%20in%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eseveral%20committees%20through%20the%201980s.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwomen%2Fbetween-history-and-histrionics%5C%22%3EBetween%20History%20and%20Histrionics%2C%20the%20Nari%20Shakti%20Vandan%20Adhiniyam%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThus%20the%201980s%20saw%20discussion%20picking%20up%20on%20both%2C%20the%20aspect%20of%20participatory%20governance%20at%20the%20local%20level%20and%20the%20absence%20of%20women%20in%20these%20processes%20%E2%80%93%20the%20latter%20pointing%20to%20the%20dissonance%20between%20political%20institutions%20and%20the%20changing%20aspirations%20of%20women%20as%20articulated%20by%20the%20resurgent%20women%E2%80%99s%20movement.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%2064%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eth%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20Amendment%20Bill%20of%201989%20%E2%80%93%20which%20could%20not%20be%20passed%20%E2%80%93%20reflected%20the%20disappointments%20as%20well%20as%20the%20contradictions%2C%20with%20the%20women%E2%80%99s%20movement%20rejecting%20any%20attempt%20to%20be%20co-opted%20through%20a%20process%20of%20nominations%20to%20the%20local%20bodies.%20The%20making%20of%20the%2073%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Erd%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20and74%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eth%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20amendments%20to%20the%20constitution%20go%20back%2C%20in%20part%2C%20to%20this%20history%20and%20the%20coalescence%20of%20diverse%20factors.%20These%20included%3A%20the%20ground%20observations%20after%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ereservations%20for%20women%20in%20the%20local%20bodies%20in%20Karnataka%20after%20the%20passage%20of%20the%20Karnataka%20Zilla%20Parishad%2C%20Taluk%20Panchayat%20Samithis%2C%20Mandal%20Panchayats%20and%20Nyaya%20Panchayats%20Act%2C%201983%20which%20generated%20interest%20among%20women%20in%20local%20bodies.%20This%20was%20followed%20by%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eformer%20Prime%20Minister%20Rajiv%20Gandhi%E2%80%99s%20wish%20to%20introduce%20reservation%20for%20women%20as%20an%20acknowledgment%20of%20the%20fact%20that%20he%20owed%20the%20massive%20mandate%20he%20received%20in%201984%20to%20women%20voters%2C%20coupled%20with%20policy%20makers%20and%20bureaucrats%20following%20up%20on%20the%20recommendations%20of%20the%20CSWI%20who%20were%20instrumental%20in%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eensuring%20the%20passage%20of%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E73%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Erd%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20and%2074%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eth%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20Constitutional%20amendments%20for%2033%25%20reservation%20for%20women%20in%201992.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDespite%20all%20the%20cynicism%20surrounding%20discussions%20on%20the%20two%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20amendments%20in%20the%20higher%20echelons%20of%20society%2C%20the%20enthusiasm%20it%20generated%20amongst%20the%20mass%20of%20women%20was%20visible%20and%20pushed%20the%20debate%20on%20reservations%20for%20women%20in%20the%20higher%20legislative%20bodies.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20these%20were%20developments%20in%20official%20quarters%2C%20it%20was%20the%20movement%E2%80%99s%20experience%20of%20confronting%20women%E2%80%99s%20increased%20marginalisation%20that%20led%20to%20their%20engaging%20with%20the%20demand%20for%20increased%20representation%20through%20the%20legislative%20process.%20By%20the%201990s%20the%20challenge%20for%20women%20to%20assert%20their%20constitutional%20right%20to%20be%20elected%20was%20clearly%20visible%20against%20the%20backdrop%20of%20growing%20criminalisation%20and%20the%20use%20of%20muscle%20and%20money%20power%20in%20politics.%20It%20became%20even%20more%20glaring%20when%20electoral%20battles%20entered%20the%20phase%20of%20coalition%20politics.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fin-charts-what-womens-representation-in-indias-parliament-assemblies-looks-like-now%5C%22%3EIn%20Charts%3A%20What%20Women%E2%80%99s%20Representation%20in%20India%E2%80%99s%20Parliament%2C%20Assemblies%20Looks%20Like%20Now%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESenior%20bureaucrat%20Nirmala%20Buch%2C%20who%20played%20no%20small%20part%20in%20ensuring%20the%20passage%20of%20these%20critical%20amendments%2C%20observed%20that%20%E2%80%9CMyths%20were%20created%20about%20women%E2%80%99s%20disinterest%20and%20passivity%20in%20politics%2C%20and%20about%20how%20female%20relatives%20of%20influential%20politicians%20from%20the%20well-off%20sections%20merely%20occupied%20these%20seats%20while%20the%20men%20were%20the%20ones%20who%20actually%20carried%20out%20the%20tasks.%E2%80%9D%20She%20countered%20this%20with%20data%20that%20disproved%20these%20stories%20and%20documented%20the%20work%20of%20younger%2C%20first%20time%20women%20entrants%20from%20economically%20weaker%20sections%20and%20their%20participation%20and%20performance%20levels.%20She%20drew%20attention%20to%20the%20challenge%20of%20%E2%80%9Cpublic%20patriarchy%20whereby%20the%20women%20are%20included%20but%20not%20allowed%20to%20participate%20and%20their%20work%20is%20consistently%20undervalued%2C%E2%80%9D%20and%20that%20the%20women%20who%20contested%20the%20panchayat%20elections%20would%20not%20have%20been%20able%20to%20do%20so%20in%20the%20absence%20of%20reservations.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFor%20her%2C%20the%20failure%20to%20tackle%20issues%20of%20rotation%20and%20such%20matters%20reflected%20the%20lack%20of%20serious%20efforts%20to%20%E2%80%9Cresolve%20the%20issue%20of%20reservations%20in%20the%20national%20and%20state%20legislatures%20make%20it%20look%20like%20a%20tactic%20to%20divert%20attention%20from%20the%20impasse%20over%20the%20Women%E2%80%99s%20Reservation%20Bill.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%201995%20women%E2%80%99s%20organisations%20issued%20a%20clear%20statement%20that%20%E2%80%98women%E2%80%99s%20political%20participation%20needs%20to%20be%20encouraged%20by%20extending%20the%20present%20reservations%20in%20the%20panchayats%E2%80%99%20and%20demanded%20%E2%80%98at%20least%2033%25%20reservations%20in%20the%20State%20assemblies%20and%20Parliament.%E2%80%99%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20was%20issued%20by%20seven%20national%20organisations%3A%20the%20All%20India%20Democratic%20Women%E2%80%99s%20Association%20(AIDWA)%2C%20the%20All%20India%20Mahila%20Dakshata%20Samiti%20(AIMDS)%2C%20All%20India%20Women%E2%80%99s%20Conference%20(AIWC)%2C%20Centre%20for%20Women%E2%80%99s%20Development%20Studies%20(CWDS)%2C%20Joint%20Women%E2%80%99s%20Programme%20(JWP)%2C%20The%20National%20Federation%20of%20Indian%20Women%20(NFIW)%2C%20Young%20Women%E2%80%99s%20Christian%20Association%20(YWCA)%2C%20with%2099%20other%20organisations%20from%20across%20India%20supporting%20the%201995%20Declaration%20of%20the%20National%20Convention%20of%20Women%20in%20Beijing.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAhead%20of%20the%201996%20elections%2C%20these%20seven%20national%20organisations%20made%20a%20public%20appeal%20to%20national%20political%20parties%20asking%20for%20inclusion%20in%20their%20manifestos%20a%20commitment%20to%20make%20necessary%20amendments%20to%20the%20constitution%20to%20ensure%20a%20minimum%20of%20one%20third%20seats%20to%20assemblies%20and%20parliament%20for%20women%20immediately.%20Representations%20of%20women%E2%80%99s%20organisations%20met%20leaders%20of%20all%20the%20national%20parties%2C%20pushing%20for%20a%20debate%20on%20the%20subject%2C%20receiving%20diverse%20responses.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwomen%2Fwomens-reservation-bill-parliament%5C%22%3EThe%20State%2C%20Formally%2C%20Remains%20Male%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20was%20following%20up%20on%20these%20interventions%20that%20the%20United%20Front%20government%20led%20by%20Deve%20Gowda%20in%201996%20introduced%20the%2081%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Est%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20Constitution%20Amendment%20Bill%20for%2033%25%20reservation%20for%20women%20in%20legislative%20bodies.%20This%20Bill%20was%20referred%20to%20a%20Parliament%20Select%20Committee%2C%20popularly%20referred%20to%20as%20the%20Geeta%20Mukherjee%20Committee.%20Women%E2%80%99s%20organisations%20followed%20up%20their%20efforts%20with%20a%20meeting%20and%20a%20memorandum%20to%20the%20committee%20in%20November%201996.%20The%20subsequent%20history%20of%20the%20various%20versions%20of%20the%20Bill%20is%20well%20documented%2C%20including%20the%20reference%20to%20a%20second%20Parliamentary%20Committee%20on%20Law%20and%20Justice%20in%202008.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhat%20is%20not%20sufficiently%20recognised%20is%20the%20persistent%20efforts%20by%20the%20movement%20to%20gather%20support%20from%20different%20political%20parties.%20They%20engaged%20in%20continuous%20debate%20on%20the%20significance%20of%20the%20figure%20of%2033%25%20%E2%80%93%20considered%20necessary%20for%20a%20critical%20mass%20to%20make%20a%20difference%20%E2%80%93%20on%20the%20question%20of%20quota%20within%20quota%2C%20proxies%20and%20debates%20arising%20from%20restrictions%20brought%20according%20to%20the%20two-child%20norm%20in%20the%20People%E2%80%99s%20Representation%20Act%20and%20their%20gender%20implications%2C%20as%20well%20as%20the%20backlash%20elected%20women%20faced%20for%20standing%20their%20ground%20in%20the%20local%20bodies.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWomen%E2%80%99s%20organisations%20have%2C%20over%20thee%20last%20three%20decades%2C%20sustained%20a%20debate%20on%20all%20aspects%20and%20maintained%20that%20the%20Bill%20needs%20to%20be%20brought%20to%20parliament%20to%20allow%20for%20a%20constructive%20debate%20on%20all%20aspects.%20There%20is%20hardly%20any%20constitutional%20authority%20that%20the%20organisations%20did%20not%20approach%20in%20these%20decades%20to%20push%20for%20a%20debate%2C%20even%20as%20there%20was%20a%20raging%20debate%20within%20the%20movement%20with%20regard%20to%20quotas%20and%20clauses%20for%20sub-reservation.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%98Let%20the%20debate%20happen%20on%20the%20floor%20of%20the%20House%E2%80%99%20was%20the%20constant%20refrain%20from%20the%20movement%20even%20as%20parties%20scuttled%20this%20very%20debate%20in%20the%20name%20of%20a%20%E2%80%98lack%20of%20consensus.%E2%80%99%20The%20strength%20to%20persist%20with%20the%20demand%20has%20largely%20come%20from%20the%20enthusiasm%20amongst%20the%20mass%20of%20women%20based%20on%20the%20experiences%20of%20working%20with%20the%2073%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Erd%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E-74%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eth%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20amendments.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20is%20these%20women%20who%20have%20carried%20the%20campaign%2C%20asserting%20democracy%20at%20the%20grassroots%2C%20facing%20the%20wrath%20of%20vested%20interest%20all%20across%20different%20states%2C%20apart%20from%20the%20cynicism%20surrounding%20the%20dismissive%20references%20to%20proxies%20and%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cem%3Epanch%20patis%20%3C%2Fem%3E(a%20term%20coined%20for%20husbands%20of%20elected%20leaders)%20%3Cspan%3Ein%20the%20upper%20echelons.%20These%20years%20have%20seen%20a%20movement%20on%20the%20ground%20as%20well%20as%20a%20petition%20in%20the%20court%20in%202011%20for%20implementation%20of%20the%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A033%25%20reservation%20for%20women%20in%20urban%20local%20bodies%20in%20Nagaland%20after%20the%20state%20government%20opposed%20implementation%20and%20application%20of%20the%20law%20citing%20customary%20laws.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EToday%2C%20as%20the%20debate%20goes%20on%20about%20the%20need%20for%20mechanisms%20to%20make%20the%20legislation%20inclusive%20in%20terms%20of%20women%20from%20specifically%20marginalised%20groups%20and%20communities%2C%20it%20may%20be%20worthwhile%20to%20recall%20what%20the%20two%20pioneers%20of%20women%E2%80%99s%20studies%20in%20India%2C%20Sarkar%20and%20Mazumdar%2C%20pointed%20out%20in%20their%20dissent%20note%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CWhen%20one%20applies%20the%20principle%20of%20democracy%20to%20a%20society%20characterised%20by%20tremendous%20inequalities%2C%20such%20special%20protections%20are%20only%20spearheads%20to%20pierce%20through%20the%20barriers%20of%20inequality.%20An%20unattainable%20goal%20is%20as%20meaningless%20as%20a%20right%20that%20cannot%20be%20exercised.%20Equality%20of%20opportunities%20cannot%20be%20achieved%20in%20the%20face%20of%20the%20tremendous%20disabilities%20and%20obstacles%20which%20the%20social%20system%20imposes%20on%20all%20those%20sections%20whom%20traditional%20India%20treated%20as%20second%20class%20or%20even%20third%20class%20citizens.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3EIndu%20Agnihotri%20is%20a%20retired%20professor%20and%20former%20director%20of%20Centre%20for%20Women%E2%80%99s%20Development%20Studies%2C%20New%20Delhi.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1695992417000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F30153449%2FACF098D3-6123-4B67-A2E4-DCA712B4.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwomen%2Fretracing-a-history-the-antecedents-of-the-womens-reservation-bill%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22It%20is%20women%20who%20carried%20the%20campaign%2C%20asserting%20democracy%20at%20the%20grassroots%20and%20faced%20the%20wrath%20of%20vested%20interest%20across%20different%20parts%20of%20the%20country.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwomen%2Fretracing-a-history-the-antecedents-of-the-womens-reservation-bill%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Rajasthan's%20Guidelines%20For%20Coaching%20Centres%20Amid%20Rising%20Student%20Suicides%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EToppers%20won't%20be%20glorified%2C%20results%20of%20routine%20tests%20will%20be%20kept%20confidential%2C%20students%20won't%20be%20segregated%20into%20special%20batches%20based%20on%20their%20ranks%20and%20a%20policy%20will%20be%20made%20for%20easy%20exit%20and%20refund%20within%20120%20days%20-%20the%20Rajasthan%20government's%20guidelines%20for%20coaching%20institutes%20said%20amid%20the%20recent%20spate%20of%20students%20suicides%20in%20Kota.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20nine-page%20guidelines%20were%20issued%20days%20after%20the%20state%20government%20set%20up%20a%2015-member%20committee%20headed%20by%20Education%20Secretary%20Bhawani%20Singh%20Detha%20to%20examine%20the%20issue%20after%20record%20student%20suicides%20were%20reported%20in%20the%20coaching%20hub.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20guidelines%2C%20framed%20in%20consultation%20with%20the%20coaching%20institutes%20and%20stakeholders%2C%20restrict%20institutes%20from%20encouraging%20students%20below%20Class%209%20to%20take%20admission%20in%20classes%20to%20prepare%20for%20medical%20and%20engineering%20entrance%20exams.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BCoaching%20institutes%20should%20not%20encourage%20students%20below%20Class%209%20to%20take%20admission.%20They%20should%20give%20admission%20after%20screening%20tests%20and%20counselling%20students%20to%20assess%20their%20interests.%20If%20any%20registered%20student%20below%20Class%209%20wants%20to%20leave%2C%20the%20institute%20should%20provide%20a%20full%20refund%20in%20120%20days%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20guidelines%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20a%20set%20of%20other%20recommendations%20for%20institutes%20to%20ease%20mental%20pressure%20on%20students%20such%20as%20facial%20recognition%20to%20prevent%20proxy%20attendance%2C%20mandatory%20weekly%20holidays%2C%20no%20exams%20on%20the%20day%20after%20a%20holiday%20and%20a%20code%20of%20conduct%20for%20faculty%20and%20hostels.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EDistrict%20collectors%20have%20been%20asked%20to%20sensitise%20all%20stakeholders%20in%20their%20areas%20and%20ensure%20that%20the%20guidelines%20are%20followed.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThis%20year%20has%20seen%20the%20highest%20number%20of%20student%20suicides%20--%2025%20so%20far.%20Last%20year%2C%20the%20figure%20was%2015.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20guidelines%20state%20legal%20action%20will%20be%20taken%20against%20coaching%20institutes%20found%20violating%20the%20code%20of%20conduct.%20The%20regulations%20also%20mention%20a%20monitoring%20cell%20for%20the%20institutes%20to%20be%20set%20up%20in%20Kota%20and%20Sikar.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20cell%20will%20have%20data%20of%20all%20the%20students%20in%20the%20coaching%20institutes%20through%20a%20dedicated%20portal%20that%20will%20be%20developed%20soon%20by%20the%20state%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20guidelines%20have%20a%20provision%20for%20an%20%26quot%3Beasy%20exit%20and%20refund%20policy%26quot%3B%20within%20120%20days%20if%20students%20and%20parents%20feel%20any%20inconvenience%20and%20uneasiness.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIt%20also%20directs%20institutes%20to%20decide%20batches%20alphabetically%20instead%20of%20by%20the%20students'%20ranks%20and%20to%20not%20shuffle%20and%20segregate%20them%20in%20the%20middle%20of%20the%20course%20based%20on%20performances%20in%20weekly%20assessments.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20guidelines%20also%20instruct%20the%20coaching%20institutes%20to%20not%20publish%20the%20results%20of%20routine%20tests%20in%20public%20and%20that%20they%20should%20counsel%20the%20students%20individually%2C%20keeping%20their%20mark%20sheets%20confidential.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAdditionally%2C%20the%20guidelines%20prohibit%20the%20glorification%20of%20toppers%20by%20coaching%20institutes.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Rajasthan%20government%20drafted%20a%20bill%20in%202022%20to%20prohibit%20institutes%20from%20glorifying%20the%20success%20of%20toppers%20but%20it%20was%20not%20tabled%20in%20assembly.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20new%20guidelines%20also%20include%20mandatory%20gatekeeper%20training%20for%20the%20teachers%2C%20institute%20managers%2C%20other%20staff%2C%20and%20the%20wardens%20of%20hostels%20and%20paying%20guest%20accommodations%20to%20assess%20the%20students'%20behavioural%20changes%20and%20take%20preventive%20measures.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20trilateral%20memorandum%20of%20understanding%20will%20be%20signed%20with%20the%20National%20Institute%20of%20Mental%20Health%20and%20Neurosciences%20(NIMHANS)%2C%20the%20state%20government%20and%20the%20people%20who%20daily%20communicate%20with%20the%20students%20such%20as%20coaching%20institutes%20and%20the%20hostel%20management%20for%20such%20training%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20guidelines%20say.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20institutes%20have%20also%20been%20directed%20to%20appoint%20a%20sufficient%20number%20of%20professional%20psychiatrists%20and%20counsellors%2C%20who%20should%20be%20%26quot%3Brecruited%20by%20NIMHANS%20or%20any%20psychology%20expert%20from%20a%20government%20medical%20college%26quot%3B%2C%20to%20keep%20a%20regular%20check%20on%20the%20students'%20psychological%20health.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20students%20will%20also%20have%20to%20be%20counselled%20regularly.%20The%20first%20counselling%20should%20be%20done%20within%2045%20days%20of%20admission%2C%20followed%20by%20the%20second%20one%20after%2090%20days%20and%20the%20third%20one%20in%20120%20days.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EVulnerable%20students%20assessed%20during%20counselling%20should%20be%20given%20optional%20career%20counselling%2C%20it%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOver%202.5%20lakh%20students%20move%20to%20Kota%20annually%20to%20prepare%20for%20competitive%20exams%20such%20as%20the%20Joint%20Entrance%20Exam%20(JEE)%20for%20engineering%20and%20the%20National%20Eligibility-cum-Entrance%20Test%20(NEET)%20for%20admission%20to%20medical%20colleges.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWith%20the%20record%20spike%20in%20suicide%20cases%2C%20the%20administration%20has%20taken%20several%20steps%2C%20including%20mandating%20the%20installation%20of%20an%20anti-hanging%20device%20in%20fans%20and%20ordering%20coaching%20institutes%20to%20not%20take%20any%20exam%20for%20two%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20anti-hanging%20device%20installation%20has%20been%20encouraged%20by%20the%20Kota%20Hostel%20Association%20since%202017%20and%20finally%20mandated%20by%20the%20district%20administration%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAnti-suicide%20nets%26quot%3B%20are%20also%20being%20installed%20in%20balconies%20and%20lobbies%20of%20hostels%20in%20Kota%20to%20prevent%20students%20from%20dying%20by%20suicide.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20police%20in%20Kota%20are%20also%20roping%20in%20wardens%2C%20mess%20workers%20and%20tiffin%20service%20providers%20to%20look%20for%20any%20signs%20of%20depression%20or%20stress%20in%20the%20students%20staying%20in%20hostels%20and%20paying%20guest%20accommodations.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20wardens%20are%20being%20encouraged%20to%20participate%20actively%20in%20the%20%26quot%3B%3Cem%3Edarwaze%20pe%20dastak%3C%2Fem%3E%20(knock%20on%20the%20door)%26quot%3B%20campaign%2C%20the%20police%20have%20urged%20the%20mess%20workers%20and%20tiffin%20service%20providers%20to%20report%20if%20a%20student%20is%20absent%20from%20the%20mess%20repeatedly%20or%20skips%20meals.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1695992160000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-08%2Fb6eobg88_kota-_625x300_28_August_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Frajasthan-guidelines-for-coaching-centres-amid-rising-student-suicides-4435350%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Rajasthan%20has%20made%20recommendations%20for%20guidelines%20for%20coaching%20institutes%20amid%20the%20recent%20spate%20of%20student%20suicides%20in%20Kota.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Frajasthan-guidelines-for-coaching-centres-amid-rising-student-suicides-4435350%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Frajasthan-guidelines-for-coaching-centres-amid-rising-student-suicides-4435350%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Frajasthan-guidelines-for-coaching-ce