entencing%20cases%20involving%20children%20in%20this%20age%20group.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TIMESOFINDIA.COM%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Findia%2Fnot-advisable-to-tinker-with-existing-age-of-consent-under-pocso-act-law-commission-to-govt%2Farticleshow%2F104044766.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22M.S.%20Swaminathan%20Will%20Forever%20Be%20Remembered%20in%20the%20Hearts%20of%20Millions%20of%20Farmers%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F29170658%2Fmss-swaminathan.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20there%20are%20a%20few%20words%20of%20English%20that%20almost%20every%20Indian%20farmer%20would%20know%2C%20those%20would%20be%20%E2%80%98Swaminathan%20Report%E2%80%99%20or%20%E2%80%98Swaminathan%20Commission%20Report.%E2%80%99%20They%20also%20know%20what%20for%20them%20is%20its%20main%20recommendation%3A%20Minimum%20Support%20Price%20%3D%20Comprehensive%20Cost%20of%20Production%20%2B%2050%25%20(also%20known%20as%20C2%2B50%25).%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EProfessor%20M.S.%20Swaminathan%20will%20be%20remembered%20not%20merely%20in%20the%20halls%20of%20government%20and%20bureaucracy%2C%20or%20even%20the%20institutions%20of%20science%20%E2%80%93%20but%20mainly%20in%20the%20hearts%20of%20millions%20of%20peasants%20demanding%20the%20implementation%20of%20the%20Report%20of%20the%20National%20Commission%20for%20Farmers%20(NCF).%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIndian%20farmers%2C%20though%2C%20simply%20call%20it%20the%20Swaminathan%20Report%20%E2%80%93%20because%20of%20the%20huge%20input%2C%20impact%20and%20indelible%20imprint%20he%20made%20on%20the%20reports%20of%20the%20NCF%2C%20of%20which%20he%20was%20chairman.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20story%20of%20the%20reports%20is%20one%20of%20betrayal%20and%20suppression%20by%20both%20the%20UPA%20and%20NDA%20governments.%20The%20first%20of%20the%20reports%20was%20submitted%20in%20December%202004%2C%20the%20fifth%20and%20final%20one%20around%20October%202006.%20Let%20alone%20a%20special%20session%20of%20parliament%20on%20the%20agrarian%20crisis%20%E2%80%93%20which%20is%20what%20we%20desperately%20need%20%E2%80%93%20not%20even%20an%20hour%E2%80%99s%20dedicated%20discussion%20was%20ever%20held.%20And%20it%20is%20now%2019%20years%20since%20the%20first%20report%20was%20submitted.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%202014%2C%20the%20Modi%20government%20came%20to%20power%2C%20to%20some%20degree%20aided%20by%20a%20promise%20they%20made%20of%20speedily%20implementing%20the%20Swaminathan%20Report%2C%20especially%20its%20MSP%20formula%20recommendation.%20Instead%2C%20the%20incoming%20government%20speedily%20filed%20an%20affidavit%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20saying%20that%20would%20not%20be%20feasible%20as%20it%20would%20distort%20market%20prices.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EPerhaps%20the%20reasoning%20of%20the%20UPA%20and%20NDA%20was%20that%20the%20reports%20were%20too%20%E2%80%9Cpro-farmer%E2%80%9D%2C%20while%20both%20governments%20were%20trying%20to%20hand%20over%20Indian%20farming%20to%20the%20corporate%20sector.%20The%20report%20was%20the%20first%20thing%20approaching%20a%20positive%20blueprint%20for%20agriculture%20since%20Independence.%20Helmed%20by%20a%20man%20who%20sought%20an%20entirely%20different%20framework%3A%20that%20we%20measure%20growth%20in%20agriculture%20in%20terms%20of%20growth%20of%20farmers%E2%80%99%20income%2C%20not%20merely%20in%20increased%20output.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EPersonally%2C%20the%20abiding%20memory%20I%20have%20of%20him%20goes%20back%20to%202005%2C%20when%20he%20was%20NCF%20chairperson%2C%20and%20I%20appealed%20to%20him%20to%20visit%20Vidarbha.%20Farmer%20suicides%20in%20the%20region%20were%20then%20occurring%20at%20the%20rate%20of%206-8%20a%20day%20in%20some%20seasons.%20Things%20were%20as%20miserable%20as%20they%20could%20be%2C%20though%20you%20wouldn%E2%80%99t%20learn%20that%20from%20most%20of%20your%20media.%20(In%202006%2C%20we%20counted%20just%20six%20journalists%20from%20outside%20Vidarbha%20who%20were%20covering%20what%20was%20perhaps%20the%20largest%20wave%20of%20suicides%20in%20recorded%20history%20in%20the%20six%20worst-hit%20districts%20of%20the%20region.%20At%20the%20same%20time%2C%20the%20Lakme%20Fashion%20Week%20in%20Mumbai%20was%20being%20covered%20by%20512%20accredited%20journalists%20and%20about%20100%20more%20on%20daily%20passes.%20The%20Fashion%20Week%E2%80%99s%20theme%20ironically%2C%20was%20cotton%20%E2%80%93%20elegantly%20presented%20on%20the%20ramp%20while%20men%2C%20women%20and%20children%20who%20grew%20that%20cotton%20were%20taking%20their%20lives%20in%20unprecedented%20numbers%20an%20hour%E2%80%99s%20flight%20away.)%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBut%20back%20to%202005.%20Prof%20Swaminathan%20responded%20to%20that%20appeal%20from%20us%20journalists%20covering%20Vidarbha%20much%20faster%20than%20any%20of%20us%20had%20expected%20and%20arrived%20there%20very%20soon%20after%20with%20an%20NCF%20team.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Vilasrao%20Deshmukh%20government%20was%20alarmed%20by%20his%20visit%20and%20tried%20their%20best%20to%20give%20him%20a%20guided%20tour%20which%20would%20keep%20him%20in%20many%20discussions%20with%20bureaucrats%20and%20technocrats%2C%20ceremonies%20at%20agricultural%20colleges%2C%20and%20more.%20The%20soul%20of%20politeness%2C%20he%20told%20the%20Maharashtra%20government%20he%20would%20visit%20the%20places%20they%20wished%20him%20to%20%E2%80%93%20but%20that%20he%20would%20also%20spend%20time%20in%20the%20field%20at%20the%20places%20I%20asked%20him%20to%20go%20to%20along%20with%20me%20and%20fellow%20journalists%20like%20Jaideep%20Hardikar.%3Cbr%3E%20And%20he%20did.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20Wardha%2C%20we%20took%20him%20to%20the%20house%20of%20Shyamrao%20Khatale%2C%20whose%20sons%2C%20the%20working%20farmers%20in%20the%20household%2C%20had%20taken%20their%20own%20lives.%20We%20arrived%20to%20find%20that%20Shyamrao%20had%20passed%20away%20a%20few%20hours%20earlier%20%E2%80%93%20of%20ill%20health%2C%20exacerbated%20by%20hunger%2C%20and%20unable%20to%20cope%20with%20the%20loss%20of%20his%20sons.%20The%20state%20government%20tried%20to%20amend%20the%20route%20saying%20the%20man%20was%20dead.%20Swaminathan%20insisted%20he%20would%20visit%20to%20pay%20his%20respects%20and%20did.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20next%20few%20house%20visits%2C%20he%20was%20in%20tears%20listening%20to%20the%20families%20of%20those%20who%20had%20ended%20their%20own%20lives.%20He%20also%20attended%20a%20memorable%20gathering%20of%20distressed%20farmers%20in%20Waifad%2C%20Wardha%2C%20organised%20by%20the%20redoubtable%20Vijay%20Jawandhia%20%E2%80%93%20one%20of%20our%20finest%20intellectuals%20on%20matters%20agrarian.%20At%20one%20point%2C%20an%20elderly%20farmer%20in%20the%20crowd%20stood%20up%20and%20asked%20him%20angrily%20why%20the%20government%20hated%20them%20so%20much.%20Should%20we%20become%20terrorists%20to%20be%20heard%3F%20The%20professor%2C%20deeply%20pained%2C%20addressed%20him%20and%20his%20friends%20with%20great%20patience%20and%20understanding.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESwaminathan%20was%20already%20in%20his%2080s.%20I%20marvelled%20at%20his%20stamina%2C%20calm%20and%20graciousness.%20We%20also%20observed%20how%20sincerely%20he%20would%20engage%20with%20people%20who%20were%20strongly%20critical%20of%20his%20opinions%20and%20work.%20How%20patiently%20he%20would%20listen%20%E2%80%93%20and%20even%20concede%20%E2%80%93%20to%20some%20of%20their%20criticisms.%20No%20one%20else%20I%20knew%20would%20so%20readily%20invite%20his%20critics%20to%20a%20seminar%20or%20workshop%20he%20was%20organising%20to%20say%20publicly%20the%20things%20they%20had%20told%20him%20personally.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20surely%20one%20of%20the%20most%20impressive%20characteristics%20of%20the%20man%20that%20he%20could%20look%20back%20over%20decades%20and%20address%20what%20he%20now%20saw%20as%20the%20failures%20and%20shortcomings%20in%20his%20own%20work.%20He%20was%20shocked%2C%20and%20said%20so%2C%20by%20the%20way%20and%20the%20scale%20at%20which%20the%20use%20of%20chemical%20fertilisers%20and%20pesticides%20went%20so%20wildly%20out%20of%20control%20with%20the%20Green%20Revolution%2C%20something%20he%20had%20not%20envisaged%20or%20imagined.%20Over%20decades%2C%20he%20grew%20more%20and%20more%20sensitive%20to%20ecology%20and%20environment%2C%20to%20the%20use%20and%20abuse%20of%20water%20resources.%20In%20the%20last%20few%20years%2C%20he%20also%20grew%20increasingly%20critical%20of%20the%20unregulated%2C%20reckless%20spread%20of%20Bt%20or%20genetically%20modified%20crops.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWith%20the%20passing%20of%20Mankombu%20Sambasivan%20Swaminathan%2C%20India%20has%20lost%20not%20just%20its%20foremost%20agricultural%20scientist%2C%20but%20a%20great%20mind%20and%20a%20fine%20human%20being.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fauthor%2Fp-sainath%5C%22%3EP.%20Sainath%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20founder%20and%20editor%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fwww.ruralindiaonline.org%2F%5C%22%3EPeople%E2%80%99s%20Archive%20of%20Rural%20India.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1695987797000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F29170658%2Fmss-swaminathan.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fagriculture%2Fms-swaminathan-obituary-p-sainath%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Through%20the%20reports%20of%20the%20National%20Commission%20for%20Farmers%2C%20the%20agricultural%20scientists%20proposed%20that%20we%20measure%20growth%20in%20agriculture%20in%20terms%20of%20growth%20of%20farmers%E2%80%99%20income%20and%20not%20merely%20increased%20output.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A12%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fagriculture%2Fms-swaminathan-obituary-p-sainath%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22If%20There%20Was%20Political%20Will%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20Raging%20Cost%20of%20