e%20A).%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F29143354%2FCLC1.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22936%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F29143354%2FCLC1.png%20936w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F29143354%2FCLC1-300x171.png%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-677500%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22532%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EFig%20A.%20Consumer%20Confidence%20Index%20Sep%202021%20%E2%80%93%20Jul%202023.%20Source%3A%20RBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhat%20you%20will%20see%20is%20recovery.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20the%20consumer%20confidence%20(current%20situation)%20index.%20It%20is%20supposed%20to%20give%20a%20sense%20as%20to%20how%20optimistic%20or%20pessimistic%20consumers%20are%20regarding%20their%20expected%20financial%20situation%20and%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20economic%20condition.%20Consumer%20optimism%20indicates%20they%20will%20spend%20more%20and%20stimulate%20the%20economy.%20Consumer%20pessimism%20can%20lead%20to%20postponing%20spending%20and%20thus%20stagnation.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20graph%20above%2C%20it%20does%20look%20as%20if%20after%20the%20pandemic%2C%20things%20are%20getting%20back%20into%20shape%20%E2%80%93%20a%20nice%20linear%20projection%20trend%20that%20will%20validate%20the%20claims%20of%20the%20government.%20But%20that%E2%80%99s%20the%20thing%20with%20statistics%2C%20they%20can%20hide%20more%20than%20they%20reveal%20unless%20we%20clarify%20our%20reference%20points%20and%20ask%20a%20few%20probing%20questions.%20In%20this%20instance%2C%20let%E2%80%99s%20just%20zoom%20out%20and%20see%20the%20picture%20below%20(Figure%20B).%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F29143545%2FCLC2.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22984%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F29143545%2FCLC2.png%20984w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F29143545%2FCLC2-300x173.png%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-677501%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22568%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EFig%20B.%20Consumer%20Confidence%20Index%20Mar%202015%20%E2%80%93%20Mar%202023.%20Source%3A%20RBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3EVoila!%20The%20optimism%20disappears.%20The%20linear%20trend%20projection%20seems%20to%20be%20only%20an%20optical%20illusion%20created%20by%20the%20preceding%20sharp%20dip%20caused%20by%20the%20pandemic%20and%20harsh%20lockdowns.%20We%20don%E2%80%99t%20really%20need%20a%20graph%20to%20validate%20that%20people%20are%20buying%20relatively%20more%20than%20in%20the%20depths%20of%20the%20lockdowns%20and%20deaths.%20So%20Figure%20A%20hardly%20merits%20celebration.%20It%20is%20Figure%20B%20that%20is%20more%20important%20and%20worrying.%20It%20is%20also%20probably%20the%20only%20phenomenon%20under%20the%20present%20government%20that%20can%20be%20characterised%20by%20the%20word%20%E2%80%9Csecular%E2%80%9D.%20As%20it%20shows%20that%20the%20general%20trend%20has%20been%20a%20secular%20fall%20from%202015%20onwards%20(see%20the%20trend%20line).%20It%20is%20symptomatic%20of%20the%20slump%20in%20demand%20that%20in%20fact%20preceded%20the%20pandemic.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20latest%20results%20of%20the%20consumer%20confidence%20survey%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Frbidocs.rbi.org.in%2Frdocs%2FPublications%2FPDFs%2FCCSJULY2023958360FCB15447479F69824DB1D1D6A7.PDF%5C%22%3ERBI%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20fact%20shows%20that%20the%20current%20situation%20index%20has%20dipped%20again%20in%20July%202023%20and%20is%20a%20shade%20lower%20than%20the%20previous%20survey.%20Overall%2C%20it%20shows%20a%20downward%20slippage%20from%20108.6%20points%20in%20the%20round%20of%20March%202015%20to%2088.1%20points%20in%20July%202023.%20The%20declaration%20of%20Amrit%20Kaal%20from%20the%20Red%20Fort%20does%20not%20seem%20to%20have%20given%20much%20confidence%20to%20the%20citizens.%20As%20far%20as%20future%20expectations%20are%20concerned%2C%20except%20for%20the%20grim%20outlook%20about%20prices%2C%20the%20survey%20otherwise%20shows%20a%20marginal%20positivity.%20But%20again%20if%20one%20zooms%20out%2C%20the%20future%20expectation%20index%20has%20in%20fact%20slid%20down%20from%20126.7%20in%20March%202015%20to%20116.6%20in%20July%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20new%20beast%20to%20worry%20about%2C%20however%2C%20is%20the%20cost%20of%20living%20crisis.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20retail%20inflation%20remains%20high%20at%206.83%25%20in%20August%202023%20after%20a%2015-month%20high%20of%207.44%25%20in%20July.%20What%20may%20appear%20to%20be%20a%20slight%20dent%20needs%20to%20be%20qualified%20with%20the%20fact%20that%20it%20is%20on%20top%20of%20an%20already%20high%20base%20of%20August%202022.%20There%20has%20been%20an%20increase%20in%20the%20inflation%20rate%20of%20fuel%20and%20light%20segment%20from%203.67%25%20to%204.31%25%20which%20remains%20worrying.%20What%20the%20numbers%20often%20don%E2%80%99t%20end%20up%20conveying%20are%20the%20social%20implications%20of%20the%20cost%20of%20living%20crisis%20and%20the%20ways%20of%20coping%20the%20poor%20are%20forced%20into.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20last%20two%20years%2C%20the%20invasion%20of%20Ukraine%20and%20supply%20cuts%20by%20Saudi%20Arabia%20and%20other%20OPEC%2B%20nations%20have%20pushed%20up%20fuel%20prices%20at%20an%20astonishing%20pace%20which%20was%20closely%20followed%20by%20a%20rising%20tide%20of%20food%20price%20inflation.%20Added%20to%20this%20was%20the%20continued%20levy%20of%20astronomical%20taxes%20on%20fuels%20at%20retail%20outlets%20by%20the%20Union%20government.%20The%20unorganised%20sector%20in%20particular%20(that%20employs%20nearly%2085%25%20of%20workers)%20where%20wages%20are%20never%20adjusted%20for%20inflation%2C%20has%20suffered%20the%20brunt%2C%20its%20back%20being%20broken%20by%20the%20successive%20shocks%20of%20demonetisation%2C%20GST%20and%20finally%20the%20sudden%20and%20harsh%20lockdowns.%20In%20FY%202022-23%2C%20the%20gross%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livemint.com%2Feconomy%2Fmint-explainer-how-inflation-is-hurting-indias-household-financial-savings-11695124010070.html%23%3A~%3Atext%3DSummary%26amp%3Btext%3DIndia%2527s%2520%2520household%2520%2520savings%2520have%2520%2520touched%2CFY21%2520to%25207.2%2525%2520in%2520FY22%5C%22%3Esavings%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20Indian%20households%20stood%20at%205.1%25%20of%20GDP%2C%20the%20lowest%20in%20at%20least%2023%20years.%20While%20during%20the%20pandemic%2C%20it%20is%20the%20lack%20of%20work%20and%20incomes%20that%20ate%20into%20the%20meagre%20savings%20of%20the%20poor%2C%20by%20the%20time%20they%20were%20hoping%20to%20recover%2C%20the%20steep%20rise%20in%20prices%20has%20once%20again%20been%20further%20depleting%20their%20savings%20as%20incomes%20have%20hardly%20been%20able%20to%20keep%20pace%20with%20inflation.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EFor%20instance%2C%20while%20the%20wages%20of%20construction%20workers%20and%20agricultural%20workers%20have%20increased%20by%20only%2010.5%25%20and%2012%25%20respectively%20in%20rural%20India%20from%20April%202021%20to%20March%202023%2C%20the%20cost%20of%20cereals%20have%20increased%20by%20a%20whopping%2022%25.%20Add%20to%20it%20the%20fuel%20segment%20of%20the%20index%20that%20has%20increased%20by%2016%25%20and%20the%20cost%20of%20milk%20and%20milk%20products%20that%20has%20increased%20by%2014%25.%20Higher%20price%20prevailing%20in%20the%20retail%20market%20effectively%20shrinks%20the%20disposable%20income%20in%20the%20hands%20of%20the%20people%2C%20which%20in%20turn%20acts%20as%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businesstoday.in%2Fmagazine%2Fdeep-dive%2Fstory%2Fbattered-by-inflation-and-faltering-demand-indias-consumer-goods-industry-is-ailing-399174-2023-09-21%5C%22%3Edampener%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20demand%20for%20consumer%20products%20as%20people%20postpone%20non-essential%20purchases.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EFigure%20C%20below%20shows%20the%20gap%20between%20the%20wages%20of%20construction%20workers%20as%20compared%20to%20fuel%20prices%2C%20and%20food%20and%20beverages%20prices%20in%20rural%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F29151157%2FCLC3.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22979%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F29151157%2FCLC3.png%20979w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F29151157%2FCLC3-300x166.png%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-677511%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22543%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EFig%20C%3A%20Annual%20Variation%3A%20CPI%20%E2%80%93%20R%20across%20(food%20%26amp%3B%20beverages%20%26amp%3B%20Fuel%20%26amp%3B%20Light)%20and%20Rural%20Wage%20Rate.%3Cbr%3ENote%3A%20Annual%20Variation%20is%20computed%20by%20taking%20the%20annual%20average%20of%20months%20in%20a%20FY%20%26amp%3B%20annual%20avg.%20of%20monthly%20wage%20rate%20(CPI%20Base%20Year%20%3A%202012%20%3D%20100).%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3EAcross%20the%20food%20and%20beverages%20and%20fuel%20and%20light%20segments%20under%20the%20rural%20component%20of%20the%20index%2C%20there%20has%20been%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.pib.gov.in%2FWriteReadData%2Fspecificdocs%2Fdocuments%2F2023%2Fsep%2Fdoc2023912250801.pdf%5C%22%3Eupward%3C%2Fa%3E%20trend.%20During%20FY%202015-16%2C%20the%20annual%20average%20of%20months%20of%20the%20index%20stood%20at%20118.4%20and%20124.4%20points%2C%20which%20have%C2%A0%20reached%20189.5%20and%20185.9%20with%20an%20inflation%20rate%20around%208.9%25%20and%203.8%25%20respectively%20in%20August.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20alarming%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fopinion%2Fcolumns%2Fjean-dreze-writes-wages-are-the-worry-not-just-unemployment-8553226%2F%5C%22%3Estagnation%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20real%20wages%2C%20as%20highlighted%20by%20economist%20Jean%20Dreze%2C%20encapsulates%20the%20crisis.%20The%20growth%20rate%20of%20real%20wages%2C%20he%20goes%20on%20to%20show%2C%20was%20below%201%25%20per%20year%20between%202014-15%20and%202021-22.%20It%20was%200.9%25%20for%20agricultural%20labour%20and%200.2%25%20for%20construction%20workers.%20It%20is%20pertinent%20to%20look%20at%20the%20recently%20released%20State%20of%20Working%20India%20Report%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcse.azimpremjiuniversity.edu.in%2Fstate-of-working-india%2Fswi-2023%2F%5C%22%3E2023%3C%2Fa%3E%20which%20captures%20the%20phenomenon%20of%20a%20dramatic%20rise%20in%20self-employed%20workers%2C%20particularly%20among%20women%2C%20since%20the%20pandemic.%20This%20is%20another%20factor%20that%20pulls%20the%20real%20wages%20down%2C%20given%20that%20the%20self-employed%20saw%20the%20highest%20fall%20in%20earnings%20in%20recent%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIs%20war%20the%20only%20factor%20contributing%20to%20the%20price%20rise%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20government%20is%20happy%20to%20externalise%20the%20crisis%20to%20the%20invasion%20of%20Ukraine%20alone%20and%20its%20effect%20on%20fuel%20prices%2C%20if%20one%20again%20looks%20at%20Figure%20C%20one%20sees%20that%20post%20FY%202020-21%2C%20it%20is%20the%20food%20inflation%20that%20has%20seen%20a%20much%20sharper%20upward%20swing.%20What%20is%20most%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.networkideas.org%2Ffeatured-articles%2F2023%2F09%2Fthe-anatomy-of-inflation%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DChandrasekhar%2520and%2520Jayati%2520Ghosh%26amp%3Btext%3DAs%2520news%2520broke%2520that%2520the%2C191.2%2520mm%2520recorded%2520in%25201905.%5C%22%3Edisconcerting%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20the%20economists%20is%20the%20fact%20that%20this%20has%20relatively%20been%20a%20time%20of%20comfortable%20levels%20of%20domestic%20food%20production.%20As%20such%2C%20the%20impact%20of%20the%20apprehended%20below%20normal%20monsoon%20on%20food%20production%20and%20thereby%20on%20the%20already%20high%20food%20prices%20is%20worrying.%20Ironically%20the%20high%20food%20prices%20did%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindubusinessline.com%2Fdata-stories%2Fdata-focus%2Fwhy-soaring-tomato-prices-have-not-made-farmers-rich%2Farticle67093664.ece%5C%22%3Enot%20benefit%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20farmers%20who%20grow%20the%20food.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhile%20that%20may%20be%2C%20let%E2%80%99s%20nonetheless%20look%20at%20the%20fuel%20prices%20and%20its%20supposed%20%E2%80%9Cexternality%E2%80%9D.%20One%20of%20the%20prime%20factors%20behind%20the%20fuel%20prices%20are%20the%20heavy%20taxes.%20One%20of%20the%20major%20sources%20of%20revenue%20for%20the%20Union%20government%20during%20the%20COVID%20crisis%20was%20through%20taxes%20on%20sale%20of%20fuels%20such%20as%20petrol%20and%20diesel.%20(Bulk%20of%20the%20excise%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.godigit.com%2Ffuel%2Ftaxes%2Fexcise-duty-on-petrol-and-diesel-in-india%5C%22%3Eduty%3C%2Fa%3E%20being%20an%20amalgamation%20of%20different%20cess%20and%20thereby%20the%20Union%20does%20not%20even%20have%20to%20share%20revenue%20with%20state%20governments).%20But%20it%20is%20an%20avenue%20of%20tax%20collection%20that%20hurts%20the%20common%20people%20at%20a%20time%20when%20their%20pockets%20were%20the%20shallowest%20owing%20to%20the%20pandemic.%20The%20average%20annual%20tax%20burden%20on%20fuel%20in%20the%20difficult%20years%20of%202020-21%20to%202022-23%20was%20Rs%204.07%20lakh%20crore%20(See%20Figure%20D).%20But%20was%20this%20the%20only%20avenue%20for%20raising%20this%20revenue%3F%20Far%20from%20it.%20In%20a%20country%20that%20is%20witnessing%20one%20of%20the%20most%20grotesque%20inequalities%20between%20the%20top%201%25%20and%20the%20rest%2C%20we%20could%20have%20easily%20raised%20the%20same%20or%20even%20more%20by%20taxing%20the%20wealthiest%20handful.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F29152721%2FCLC4.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22900%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F29152721%2FCLC4.png%20900w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F29152721%2FCLC4-300x155.png%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-677518%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22466%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EFig%20D%3A%20Trend%20in%20the%20revenue%20generated%20through%20taxes%20%2F%20duties%20that%C2%A0%20Union%20has%20levied%20on%20the%20petroleum%20sector%20over%20the%20years.%C2%A0Source%3A%20Petroleum%20Planning%20%26amp%3B%20Analysis%20Cell%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3EHypothetically%2C%20if%20the%20government%20was%20to%20be%20mindful%20of%20the%20enormous%20burden%20of%20rising%20prices%20that%20this%20is%20adding%20to%20the%20common%20people%E2%80%99s%20woes%20and%20had%20revised%20its%20tax%20rates%20to%20the%20pre-pandemic%20(2019-20)%20level%2C%20then%20the%20estimated%20loss%20of%20revenue%20in%20the%20difficult%20years%20would%20have%20been%20Rs%201.19%20lakh%20crore.%20If%20a%20flat%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cenfa.org%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F03%2FPrimer-on-Wealth-Inequality.pdf%5C%22%3Ewealth%20tax%3C%2Fa%3E%20rate%20of%202%25%20was%20imposed%20on%20individuals%20with%20net%20worth%20of%20Rs%201%2C000%20crore%20or%20above%20in%202021%2C%20that%20is%2C%20if%20the%20wealthiest%201%2C007%20families%20in%20the%20country%20were%20taxed%2C%20we%20could%20have%20raised%20Rs%201.84%20lakh%20crore%20in%20just%20a%20year.%20A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftaxtherichin.wordpress.com%2Fvoices-against-inequality%2F%5C%22%3Ewealth%20tax%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20this%20nature%20if%20constituted%20(as%20it%20was%20done%20in%20Argentina%2C%20Bolivia%2C%20Colombia%20and%20so%20on%20after%20the%20pandemic)%20could%20have%20helped%20us%20not%20only%20to%20shield%20the%20poor%20from%20the%20soaring%20fuel%20prices%2C%20but%20also%20recover%20better%20by%20increasing%20welfare%20spending.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EInstead%2C%20we%20tied%20ourselves%20to%20a%20K-shaped%20recovery%20wherein%20rising%20prices%20and%20dwindling%20income%20has%20forced%20the%20poor%20to%20cut%20back%20expenses%20on%20food%20and%20other%20essentials.%20Meanwhile%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livemint.com%2Fnews%2Findia%2Foff-the-mark-luxury-car-sales-roar-in-india-11690913994834.html%23%3A~%3Atext%3DAround%252021%252C000%2520luxury%2520cars%2520were%2Cthe%2520same%2520period%2520in%25202018.%255C%5C%22%3Eultra%20rich%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20spending%20on%20imported%20liquor%2C%20luxury%20cars%20and%20leisure%20as%20evidenced%20through%20both%20sales%20and%20import%20data.%20As%20per%20Credit%20Suisse%2C%20the%20number%20of%20USD%20millionaires%20in%20India%20is%20projected%20to%20more%20than%20double%20by%202026.%20Meanwhile%20we%20await%20this%20year%E2%80%99s%20hunger%20index%20as%20to%20where%20we%20move%20from%20our%20unenviable%20slippage%20to%20107th%20position.%20Grand%20events%2C%20divisive%20politics%2C%20an%20army%20of%20social%20media%20bots%20and%20a%20pliant%20traditional%20media%20have%20kept%20the%20people%20distracted%20from%20the%20pinch.%20The%20question%20is%2C%20for%20how%20long%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EAnirban%20Bhattacharya%20is%20Team%20Lead%2C%20National%20Finance%20Team%20and%20Pranay%20Singh%20is%20Data%20Analyst%20at%20Centre%20for%20Financial%20Accountability.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1695987012000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F29155126%2Frickshaw-2158447_1280.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Fif-there-was-political-will-indias-raging-cost-of-living-crisis-could-be-eased%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22While%20the%20government%20is%20happy%20to%20externalise%20the%20crisis%20to%20the%20invasion%20of%20Ukraine%20alone%20and%20its%20effect%20on%20fuel%20prices%2C%20it%20is%20the%20food%20inflation%20that%20has%20seen%20a%20much%20sharper%20upward%20swing.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A30%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Fif-there-was-political-will-indias-raging-cost-of-living-crisis-could-be-eased%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Simultaneous%20Polls%20From%202029%3F%20Law%20Commission%20Working%20On%20Formula%3A%20Report%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20Law%20Commission%20is%20working%20on%20a%20formula%20to%20synchronise%20all%20assembly%20polls%20by%20extending%20or%20reducing%20the%20tenure%20so%20states%20can%20go%20to%20polls%20along%20with%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%202029%20onwards%2C%20sources%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20government%20has%20already%20set%20up%20a%20high-level%20panel%20to%20explore%20simultaneous%20polls%20for%20Lok%20Sabha%2C%20state%20assemblies%2C%20and%20local%20bodies%2C%20the%20Law%20Commission%20may%20also%20be%20asked%20to%20include%20the%20third%20tier%20of%20elections%20along%20with%20its%20current%20mandate%20for%20national%20and%20state%20polls.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20law%20panel%20is%20devising%20a%20mechanism%20to%20ensure%20a%20common%20electoral%20roll%20for%20Lok%20Sabha%2C%20assemblies%2C%20and%20local%20bodies%20to%20reduce%20cost%20and%20use%20of%20manpower%20for%20an%20almost%20identical%20exercise%20carried%20out%20now%20by%20the%20Election%20Commission%20and%20the%20state%20election%20commissions%2C%20the%20sources%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Law%20Commission's%20report%20on%20simultaneous%20polls%20is%20not%20ready%20as%20some%20issues%20are%20yet%20to%20be%20settled%2C%20they%20pointed%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EFor%20synchronising%20various%20assembly%20polls%20to%20ensure%20both%20state%20and%20Lok%20Sabha%20elections%20are%20held%20together%20from%202029%2C%20the%20Commission%2C%20under%20Justice%20Ritu%20Raj%20Awasthi%2C%20may%20suggest%20reducing%20or%20enhancing%20the%20tenure%20of%20legislative%20assemblies.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EA%20mechanism%20is%20being%20devised%20to%20ensure%20that%20once%20Lok%20Sabha%20and%20assembly%20polls%20are%20synchronised%2C%20voters%20go%20to%20polling%20booths%20just%20once%20to%20cast%20their%20ballot%20for%20both%20elections.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESince%20assembly%20and%20parliamentary%20polls%20are%20held%20in%20phases%2C%20the%20Commission%20is%20working%20out%20modalities%20to%20see%20that%20voters%20do%20not%20have%20to%20go%20to%20the%20polling%20stations%20more%20than%20once%20for%20the%20two%20polls%2C%20they%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Commission%2C%20they%20said%2C%20is%20of%20the%20view%20that%20assembly%20and%20parliamentary%20polls%20can%20be%20held%20together%20and%20it%20is%20working%20out%20modalities%20for%20the%20smooth%20conduct%20of%20the%20mammoth%20democratic%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAs%20of%20now%20the%20mandate%20of%20the%20Commission%20is%20to%20suggest%20ways%20to%20hold%20the%20assembly%20and%20Lok%20Sabha%20polls%20together.%20But%20the%20high-level%20committee%20under%20former%20President%20Ram%20Nath%20Kovind%20has%20been%20tasked%20with%20recommending%20how%20Lok%20Sabha%2C%20assembly%2C%20and%20local%20body%20polls%20(panchayat%2C%20municipalities%2C%20zila%20parishad)%20can%20be%20held%20together.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EKeeping%20in%20mind%20the%20terms%20of%20reference%20of%20the%20Kovind%20panel%2C%20the%20ambit%20of%20the%20Law%20Commission%20can%20also%20be%20increased%20to%20include%20holding%20local%20body%20polls%20along%20with%20national%20and%20state%20polls%2C%20the%20sources%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOne%20suggestion%20the%20law%20panel%20can%20make%20is%20to%20hold%20the%20three-tier%20polls%20in%20two%20phases%20in%20a%20year.%20In%20the%20first%20phase%2C%20Lok%20Sabha%20and%20assembly%20polls%20can%20be%20held%2C%20while%20in%20the%20second%20phase%2C%20local%20bodies%20can%20go%20to%20polls.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThis%2C%20the%20sources%20said%2C%20is%20a%20practical%20approach%20keeping%20in%20mind%20the%20varied%20climatic%20conditions%20in%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20August%202018%2C%20the%20previous%20Law%20Commission%20endorsed%20the%20Modi%20government's%20proposal%20to%20hold%20simultaneous%20polls%20to%20Lok%20Sabha%20and%20state%20assemblies%2C%20saying%20it%20would%20prevent%20the%20country%20from%20being%20in%20constant%20election%20mode.%20It%20however%20sought%20further%20public%20discourse%20on%20the%20issue%20before%20arriving%20at%20a%20final%20decision.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20panel%20in%20its%20draft%20report%20had%20also%20said%20the%20exercise%20cannot%20be%20held%20in%20the%20present%20constitutional%20framework%2C%20and%20suggested%20changes%20required%20to%20carry%20out%20the%20two%20sets%20of%20polls%20together.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20April%202018%2C%20the%20law%20ministry%20asked%20the%20Law%20Commission%20to%20examine%20the%20issue%20of%20holding%20simultaneous%20polls%20to%20Lok%20Sabha%20and%20state%20assemblies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1695987000000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2020-11%2Fmpbfnv4_election-generic-afp650_625x30